<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1225,1754]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
DISTRIBUTION. Coastal Red Sea from 
<collectingCountry box="[585,652,1334,1358]" name="Egypt" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Egypt</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[691,772,1334,1357]" name="Yemen" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Yemen</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[830,925,1333,1358]" name="Somalia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, around the shores of the Arabian Peninsula, Persian Gulf coast, 
<collectingCountry box="[370,468,1369,1394]" name="Pakistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, E 
<collectingCountry box="[503,643,1369,1394]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, N 
<collectingCountry box="[681,742,1369,1394]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1225,1754]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[351,407,1406,1429]" name="Iran" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[422,506,1405,1430]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49. 44" captionStartId="79.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-60@79.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. 44. Hemidactylus flaviviridis. 45. Hemidactylus persicus. 46. Hemidactylus robustus. Question marks indicate dubious data or specimens determined as H. turcicus. 47. Hemidactylus romeshkanicus. 48. Mediodactylus aspratilis. 49. Mediodactylus heterocercum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929730/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
. Mostly along the Persian Gulf coast; a more inland record recently reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,267,1442,1465]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fars Prov.</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gholamifard, A. &amp; Gholamhosseini, A. &amp; Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Esmaeili, H. R. &amp; Kami, H. G." box="[280,556,1441,1466]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="61 - 63" refId="ref51777" refString="Gholamifard, A., Gholamhosseini, A., Rastegar-Pouyani, N., Esmaeili, H. R. &amp; Kami, H. G. (2010) First Records of Tropiocolotes steudneri Peters, 1869 and Hemidactylus flaviviridis Ruppell, 1840 (Sauria: Gekkonidae) from Fars Province, Iran. Asian Herpetological Research, 1, 61 - 63." type="journal article" year="2010">
Gholamifard 
<emphasis box="[432,489,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1225,1754]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
HABITAT. A typical house gecko bound to human settlements, ports, railway junctions etc. (
<bibRefCitation author="Gallagher, M. D." box="[1184,1363,1477,1502]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref51380" refString="Gallagher, M. D. (1971) The amphibians and reptiles of Bahrain. published by the author, Bahrain, 40 pp." type="book" year="1971">Gallagher 1971</bibRefCitation>
; Khan 2009; 
<bibRefCitation author="Das, M. &amp; Purkayastha, J. &amp; Bauer, A. &amp; Sengupta, S." box="[221,394,1513,1538]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="98 - 104" refId="ref48953" refString="Das, M., Purkayastha, J., Bauer, A. &amp; Sengupta, S. (2011) Hemidactylus flaviviridis Ruppell, 1835 (Sauria: Gekkonidae) an invasive gecko in Assam. North-Western Journal of Zoology, 7, 98 - 104." type="journal article" year="2011">
Das 
<emphasis box="[272,328,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; pers. obs).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1225,1754]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
REMARKS. Given the high affinity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1835" box="[568,723,1549,1574]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flaviviridis">
<emphasis box="[568,723,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">H. flaviviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to urban areas and human settlements it is likely that this gecko has been introduced to the western parts of its range probably from 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1023,1585,1610]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">India</collectingCountry>
by humans (
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[1180,1362,1585,1610]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
). This assumption is in agreement with the coastal distribution and low genetic variability among animals from 
<collectingCountry box="[1334,1432,1621,1646]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,235,1658,1681]" name="Yemen" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[246,317,1657,1682]" name="Oman" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Oman</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[328,426,1657,1682]" name="Pakistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[485,542,1657,1682]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Carranza, S. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J." box="[557,761,1657,1682]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="64018" refId="ref65401" refString="Smid, J., Carranza, S., Kratochvil, L., Gvozdik, V., Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J. (2013 a) Out of Arabia: A Complex Biogeographic History of Multiple Vicariance and Dispersal Events in the Gecko Genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). PLoS ONE, 8, e 64018. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0064018" type="journal article" year="2013">
Šmíd 
<emphasis box="[624,681,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
2013a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
